entry.title: Duterte: We cannot afford another wave of coronavirus infections

media:group.media:title: Duterte: We cannot afford another wave of coronavirus infections
media:group.media:description: The Philippines cannot afford another wave of coronavirus infections, President Rodrigo Duterte said Tuesday as he prepared the public for the looming easing of restrictions. Duterte, in a taped public address aired Tuesday, urged the public to wear face masks and practice physical distancing as part of the new norm.

entry.title: Marijuana ipinalaman sa tinapay, nasabat sa Pasig

media:group.media:title: Marijuana ipinalaman sa tinapay, nasabat sa Pasig
media:group.media:description: Nasabat ng mga kagawad ang isang sachet ng marijuana na ipinalaman sa tinapay na ipapadala sana sa Malabon mula Pasig.

entry.title: Duterte dangles P2 million reward for killing, capture of communist leaders

media:group.media:title: Duterte dangles P2 million reward for killing, capture of communist leaders
media:group.media:description: President Rodrigo Duterte offered Tuesday a P2 million bounty to anyone who would kill or capture a "top commander" of communist rebels. The President said informants would be treated as witnesses and would receive government protection.

entry.title: Duterte comforts mothers who lost children in COVID-19 fight

media:group.media:title: Duterte comforts mothers who lost children in COVID-19 fight
media:group.media:description: In a public address aired Tuesday, President Rodrigo Duterte sympathized with mothers who lost their children in the battle against the coronavirus pandemic.

entry.title: Philippines to hire contact-tracers 'en masse,' restart 'Build Build Build'

media:group.media:title: Philippines to hire contact-tracers 'en masse,' restart 'Build Build Build'
media:group.media:description: The Philippines will "restart and accelerate" its P8 trillion infrastructure program, hire contact-tracers "en masse" and push food production as part of efforts to reboot the economy from the COVID-19 pandemic, the head of President Rodrigo Duterte's economic team said Tuesday.

entry.title: P5,000 Makati aid open for residents of exclusive subdivisions: mayor

media:group.media:title: P5,000 Makati aid open for residents of exclusive subdivisions: mayor
media:group.media:description: Residents of exclusive subdivisions like Forbes and Dasmariñas Village can apply for the P5,000 aid that the Makati City government will give to half a million residents, Mayor Abby Binay said Tuesday.

entry.title: Temporary franchise the remedy for ABS-CBN broadcast woes: ex-DICT chief

media:group.media:title: Temporary franchise the remedy for ABS-CBN broadcast woes: ex-DICT chief
media:group.media:description: The "short and swift" remedy for ABS-CBN to continue its broadcast operation is Congress' granting of a provisional franchise, a former member of the Duterte Cabinet said Tuesday.
